#Used during get warning code to ignore the warning
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

columns_to_plot = [
    'Hydraulic_Pressure(bar)', 'Coolant_Pressure(bar)',
    'Air_System_Pressure(bar)', 'Coolant_Temperature',
    'Downtime', 'Spindle_Bearing_Temperature(C)',
    'Spindle_Vibration(m)', 'Tool_Vibration(m)', 'Spindle_Speed(RPM)',
    'Hydraulic_Oil_Temperature(C)', 'Torque(Nm)', 'Cutting(kN)'
]

# Loop through each column and create scatter plot
for column in columns_to_plot:
    plt.figure(figsize=(4, 2))  # Adjust figure size as needed
    sns.scatterplot(data=df, x=column, y='Voltage(volts)')
    plt.title(f"Scatter plot of {column} vs 'Voltage(volts)")
    plt.xlabel(column)
    plt.ylabel('Voltage(volts)')
    plt.show()

import numpy as np

def wisker(col):
    q1, q3 = np.percentile(col, [25, 75])
    iqr = q3 - q1
    lw = q1 - 1.5 * iqr
    uw = q3 + 1.5 * iqr
    return lw, uw

In [206]:
for i in ['Coolant_Pressure(bar)', 'Air_System_Pressure(bar)',
       'Coolant_Temperature', 'Hydraulic_Oil_Temperature(C)',
       'Spindle_Bearing_Temperature(C)', 'Spindle_Vibration(m)',
       'Tool_Vibration(m)', 'Spindle_Speed(RPM)', 'Voltage(volts)',
       'Torque(Nm)', 'Cutting(kN)']:
        lw,uw=wisker(df[i])
        df[i]=np.where(df[i]<lw,lw,df[i])
        df[i]=np.where(df[i]<uw,uw,df[i])
